Determine the values of `x` and `y` after the following code runs.

```java
int x = 4;
int y = 9;
x++;
y--;
y--;
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int n = 0;
n++;
n++;
n++;
n--;
System.out.println(n);
```

A student writes the following code intending to print a countdown from 5 to 1. Which change would make the code work as intended?

```java
int x = 5;
while (x > 0) {
    System.out.println(x);
    x++;
}
```

Determine the values of `a` and `b` after the following code runs.

```java
int a = 2;
int b = 6;
a++;
b--;
b--;
a += b;
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int count = 8;
while (count > 4) {
    count--;
}
System.out.println(count);
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int p = 10;
int q = 3;
p--;
p--;
q++;
System.out.println(p + " " + q);
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int n = 1;
int total = 0;
while (n <= 5) {
    total++;
    n++;
    n++;
}
System.out.println(total);
```

Determine the value of `x` after the following code runs.

```java
int x = 4;
x++;
x++;
x--;
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int val = 1;
for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
    val++;
    System.out.print(val + " ");
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 6;
int y = 3;
x--;
x--;
y++;
System.out.println(x + " " + y);
```

Determine the values of `x` and `y` after the following code runs.

```java
int x = 3;
int y = 7;
x++;
y--;
y--;
x++;
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int n = 10;
n--;
n--;
n++;
System.out.println(n);
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int x = 10;
int y = 0;
while (x > 6) {
    x--;
    y++;
}
System.out.println(x + " " + y);
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
int a = 0;
int b = 5;
for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
    a++;
    b--;
}
System.out.println(a + " " + b);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 4;
int y = 1;

x++;
y--;
x = x + y;
y++;

System.out.println(x + " " + y);
```

Determine the values of `total` and `n` after the following code runs.

```java
int total = 0;
int n = 5;

while (n > 1)
{
    total++;
    n--;
}
```
